<div style="--width:960; --height:604;"><img decoding="async" style="--twidth:960; --theight:604;" alt="thumbnail" src="" data-src="https://i.vimeocdn.com/video/1736894022-d7243cb648dd91fa16dce293375d821739901e6bc93506c363e3be159098acc8-d_960" data-srcset="" srcset=""><iframe title="Form and Agency &ndash; full website" src="" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture; clipboard-write" data-src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/873404595?dnt=1&amp;app_id=122963"></iframe></div>
</div></figure>



<p class="row2md"><strong>3. ETYM(YTH)OLOGY<br></strong><br>Throughout the identity development process, Darius crafted a fictional lore for the typeface as an integral part of the exhibition. This lore wove together a series of ideas rooted in the etymologies of the Latin alphabet, interwoven with semi-fictional myths. He published them on Instagram <a href="https://www.instagram.com/p/CxP1EbJSv_W/?img_index=7">www.instagram.com/p/CxP1EbJSv_W/?img_index=7</a>.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large" style="--width:1024; --height:1024;"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="1024" src="" alt="" class="wp-image-499" srcset="" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" data-src="/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/image-5-1-1024x1024.jpeg" data-srcset="/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/image-5-1-1024x1024.jpeg 1024w, /wp-content/uploads/2024/09/image-5-1-300x300.jpeg 300w, /wp-content/uploads/2024/09/image-5-1-150x150.jpeg 150w, /wp-content/uploads/2024/09/image-5-1-768x768.jpeg 768w, /wp-content/uploads/2024/09/image-5-1-1536x1536.jpeg 1536w, /wp-content/uploads/2024/09/image-5-1.jpeg 1886w"></figure>



<p>This is a fun work I did on top of this written, using gpt-3.5-turbo API. It&rsquo;s still a WIP because I initially attempted to fine-tune the model to better comprehend the lore, but that didn&rsquo;t go as planned. In the future, I&rsquo;m considering alternative methods, such as using embeddings, to integrate chat responses as part of the written lore.</p>



